// SmartPlug App
//
// System Architecture:
// - Communication via TCP sockets
// - Hub: Raspberry Pi 4B (Linux-based server)
// - Base Units: ESP32 (3.3V microcontrollers)
// - App communicates with Hub over local network
//
// FR2: Real-Time Monitoring
// - App polls hubs every 5 seconds
// - Retrieves status of Bases/Nodes (on/off, connection, current draw)
//
// FR5: Multi-Hub Support
// - App supports multiple hubs across rooms
// - Each hub has unique ID and independent state
//
// FR8: Setup + Secure Login
// - First-time launch shows setup page for account creation
// - Credentials are securely stored using salted + hashed passwords (PBKDF2)
// - Login persists using secure storage
// - Users remain authenticated until logout
// - Setup flow includes hub discovery for initial pairing

